{"lemma":"نَقْصُ","slug":"نَقْصُ","root":"ن.ق.ص","root_slug":"ن-ق-ص","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ق-ص","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نَقْص","root":"نقص","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40412","","n40416"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B5%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to decrease, diminish, reduce"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be reduced by (an amount)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lack"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَقَصَ (naqaṣa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reduction"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lack"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/na.qa.sˤa/","/naqsˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40412","headword_ar":"نَقَصَ","root":"nqS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqoSaAnN","text_ar":"نُقْصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoSN","text_ar":"نَقْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Msb, K,) or the former of these two only, the latter being the inf. n. of the trans. verb, (MS,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqiySapN","text_ar":"نَقِيصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanoqaASN","text_ar":"تَنْقَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [which last is an intensive form,] said of a thing, (S, M,) intrans., (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It lost somewhat, decreased, diminished, lessened, wasted, waned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became defective"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deficient"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incomplete"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperfect, after having been whole"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, lost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suffered loss"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diminution,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to lot"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AntqS","text_ar":"انتقص","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnq~S","text_ar":"تنقّص","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TK, [probably from the TA,] art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afn","text_ar":"اَفن"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnAqS","text_ar":"تناقص","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it lost somewhat, decreased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gradually; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tzAyd","text_ar":"تزايد"},{"kind":"text","text":".] It is said in a trad., (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoraA EiydK laA yanoquSaAni","text_ar":"شَهْرَا عِيدٍ لَا يَنْقُصَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, K,) i. e. Ramadán and Dhu-l-Hijjeh, (Mgh,) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two months of festival are not defective"},{"kind":"text","text":"virtually ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlHukomi","text_ar":"فِى الحُكْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") though they be defective in number [of days]; (K;) i. e. let no doubt occur in your hearts when ye fast nine and twenty days [instead of thirty]; nor if there happen a mistake respecting the day of the pilgrimage, will there be any deficiency in your performance of the rites thereof: (TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two months of festival will not be defective"},{"kind":"text","text":"in one and the same year; but Et- Taháwee disapproves of this explanation: some say that the meaning is, that though they be defective, or one of them be so, yet their recompense will be complete. (Mgh.) It is also said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a AlEamala fiY Ea$ori *iY AlHij~api laA yanoquSu","text_ar":"اـِنَّ العَمَلَ فِى عَشْرِ ذِى الحِجَّةِ لَا يَنْقُصُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawaAbuhu Eam~aA fiY $ahori ramaDaAna","text_ar":"ثَوَابُهُ عَمَّا فِى شَهْرِ رَمَضَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the deed"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is done"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the tenth of Dhu-l-Hijjeh, the recompense thereof will not fall short of that which is in the month of Ramadán:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaSa Eano ka*aA","text_ar":"نَقَصَ عَنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It fell short of such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mgh.) [On the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~uqoSaAni","text_ar":"فِى النُّقْصَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as used in grammar, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gafiyrN","text_ar":"غَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaSahu","text_ar":"نَقَصَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoSN","text_ar":"نَقْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MS,) [and accord. to the TK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanoqaASN","text_ar":"تَنْقَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqoSaAnN","text_ar":"نُقْصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, which last, however, is said in the MS to be an inf. n. of the intrans. verb only,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it to lose somewhat, decreased it, diminished it, curtailed it, lessened it, wasted it, impaired it, took from it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it defective"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deficient"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incomplete"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperfect, after it had been whole"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a share, or portion)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defective"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deficient:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [the pronoun often relates to a man: see an ex. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dwz","text_ar":"ضوز"},{"kind":"text","text":", and another in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wks","text_ar":"وكس"},{"kind":"text","text":":] this is the [most] chaste form of the verb, and is that which occurs in the Kur.: (Msb:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnqShu","text_ar":"انقصهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the same; (M, Msb, K;) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nq~Shu","text_ar":"نقّصهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanoqiySN","text_ar":"تَنْقِيصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) but these two are of weak authority, and do not occur in chaste language: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AntqShu","text_ar":"انتقصهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took from it by little and little;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnq~Shu","text_ar":"تنقّصهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, * TA [in the latter of which this is plainly said of both of the last two verbs; but in the M, it seems rather to be said of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnq~Sh","text_ar":"تنقّصه"},{"kind":"text","text":"only.]) [See an ex. of the verb followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn","text_ar":"من"},{"kind":"text","text":"voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TarafN","text_ar":"طَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaSa minohu ka*aA","text_ar":"نَقَصَ مِنْهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut off from it such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaSa","text_ar":"نَقَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is doubly trans.: (Msb:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaSahu","text_ar":"نَقَصَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~ahu","text_ar":"حَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoSN","text_ar":"نَقْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, Mgh;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~ahu","text_ar":"حَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AntqShu","text_ar":"انتقصهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, A, * Mgh, * TA; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He diminished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impaired, to him his right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due; endamaged him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him to suffer loss,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"damage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"detriment, in respect of it; curtailed him, abridged him, deprived him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defrauded him, of a portion of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awofaAhu","text_ar":"اَوْفَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he abridged him, deprived him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defrauded him, of it altogether;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaSahu A^aholahu wamaAlahu","text_ar":"نَقَصَهُ اَهْلَهُ وَمَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He deprived him of his family and his property altogether:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as appears from the following ex.:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqiSa A^aholahu wamaAlahu wabaqiYa farodFA","text_ar":"نُقِصَ اَهْلَهُ وَمَالَهُ وَبَقِىَ فَرْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was deprived of his family and his property, and remained alone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wtr","text_ar":"وتر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~i","text_ar":"الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinotiqaASu","text_ar":"اِنْتِقَاصُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The denying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disacknowledging, the right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also 5."}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","Msb","K","A","MS","IKtt","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n40416","headword_ar":"نَقْصٌ","root":"nqS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1. ―         -b2-  [Used as a subst.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Loss,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loss of somewhat, decrease, a state of diminution"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lessening"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"washing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waning, defect, defectiveness, deficiency, incompleteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperfection, after wholeness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"completeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfectness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqoSaAnN","text_ar":"نُقْصَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoqaSapN","text_ar":"مَنْقَصَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoS","text_ar":"نَقْص"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as here rendered, agreeably with the explanation (i. e. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnqSp","text_ar":"منقصة"},{"kind":"text","text":") in the PS., which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamiYo","text_ar":"كَمِىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoqaSapN","text_ar":"مَنْقَصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqiySapN","text_ar":"نَقِيصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense assigned to this last in the S, or in certain senses assigned to it in the K, which see below; and thus to be more restricted in application than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoSN","text_ar":"نَقْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness of intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weakness"},{"kind":"text","text":"with respect to religion and intellect. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala Ealayohi naqoSN fiY diynihi waEaqolihi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ عَلَيْهِ نَقْصٌ فِى دِينِهِ وَعَقْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There came upon him a weakness in his religion and his intellect"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but one should not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqoSaAnN","text_ar":"نُقْصَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in this case]: (K:) app. because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aqoS","text_ar":"النَّقْص"},{"kind":"text","text":"is “ weakness; ” whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uqoSaAnu","text_ar":"النُّقْصَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is only “ a going away [of part of a thing] after [its having been in] a state of completeness. ” (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","K"]}]}}